    dc:description "Figure 3. Samsoniella asiatica A fungus-infected lepidopteran pupa B stipes producing a mass of conidia at the apex C synnemata of fungus arising from lepidopteran larva D colony as obversed on PDA medium E-M conidiophores, phialides and conidia on PDA N conidia on PDA. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, C); 5 mm (B); 20 mm (D); 15 μm (E); 10 μm (F, G, H); 5 μm (I, J, K, N); 3 μm (L, M)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/915713" ;
